\import{dt-macros}
\title{Extending cpo Mappings to endofunctors on #{\textbf{Cpo}^\mathbf{R}}}
\author{liamoc}
\p{If #{\mathcal{F}} is a mapping on [cpos](dt-001D) built up from basic cpos using the constructions #{\times}, #{\otimes}, #{+}, #{\oplus}, #{(\cdot)_\bot}, \em{as well as} #{\contto} and #{\strictto}, then #{\mathcal{F}} extends to a (\em{covariant}!) [cocontinuous functor](dt-005E) on #{\textbf{Cpo}^\mathbf{R}}. 
We shall detail the construction for products and functions here, but the other constructions are all similar.}
